This paper deals with the problem of imitation learning in a challenging setting where the agent and the expert use different actions from each other. This problem is relevant to several areas of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), systems and control (cs.SY), and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a method that combines imitation learning and reinforcement learning to address this problem, which further supports the relevance of the paper to these sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, and cs.CV.
